Buckhorn Inc said itd ninemillion dlr backlog for orders and a less expensive operatingenvironment should yield significant levels of operatingprofits for 1987.    Buckhorn, a manufacturer of reusable plastic shipping andstorage containers, recorded 2,051,000, or 1.55 dlrs per share,operating net loss for 1986.    Buckhorn said the year's results included a 4,250,000non-recurring expense incurred to complete major restructuringefforts and to defend against the hostile tender offer fromRopak Corporation.    Reuter&#3;